# Constant Fold String Functions

## Description

Evaluates string functions (UPPER, LOWER, LENGTH, CONCAT, SUBSTRING,
TRIM, REPLACE) at compile time when all arguments are literal strings.

**When to apply**: String function with all-constant arguments.

**Why it works**: String functions are deterministic. String operations
can be especially expensive per row; folding eliminates allocation.

## Relational Algebra

```algebra
pi[UPPER('hello')](R) -> pi['HELLO'](R)
pi[LENGTH('world')](R) -> pi[5](R)
pi[CONCAT('a', 'b', 'c')](R) -> pi['abc'](R)
```

## Implementation

```rust
rw!("fold-upper"; "(upper ?a)" => { FoldStr("?a", str::to_uppercase) } if is_const("?a")),
rw!("fold-lower"; "(lower ?a)" => { FoldStr("?a", str::to_lowercase) } if is_const("?a")),
rw!("fold-length"; "(length ?a)" => { FoldStr("?a", |s| s.len()) } if is_const("?a")),
rw!("fold-concat"; "(concat ?a ?b)" => { FoldStr2("?a", "?b", concat) } if both_const("?a", "?b")),
rw!("fold-substring";
    "(substring ?a ?start ?len)" => { FoldSubstr("?a", "?start", "?len") }
    if all_const("?a", "?start", "?len")
),
rw!("fold-trim"; "(trim ?a)" => { FoldStr("?a", str::trim) } if is_const("?a")),
rw!("fold-replace";
    "(replace ?a ?from ?to)" => { FoldReplace("?a", "?from", "?to") }
    if all_const("?a", "?from", "?to")
),
```

## Test Cases

```sql
-- Before
SELECT id, UPPER('hello') || ' ' || LOWER('WORLD') FROM t;
-- After
SELECT id, 'HELLO world' FROM t;
```

```sql
-- Negative: column argument
SELECT UPPER(name) FROM users;
-- Cannot fold: name is a column
```

